# IX Interaction Pattern Decision Tree

Use this rule when picking which pattern to use for a new view or interaction. The pattern determines which `@procore/core-react` primitive and which scaffold template to reach for.

## Decision tree

- Creating a **new record** → **Pattern 3 Slide-Out** (`@procore/core-react` `Tearsheet`, scaffold Tearsheet template at 37%/63% width, z-30, right-to-left). Save/Cancel is the current scaffold default; server-side autosave is a `toolinator-proposal` (see `TOOLINATOR-EXTENSIONS.md`).
- Reviewing / editing **an existing record alongside a list** → **Pattern 1 Split-View** (`SplitViewCard` primitives via the `SplitViewShell` template; 37% list left, 63% detail right).
- Viewing complex info that **needs full width** → **Pattern 2 Full-Workspace** (`ToolLandingPage` / `DetailPage` / `SettingsPage` layouts via Toolinator).
- **Detail + supplemental context** (comments, activity) → **Pattern 4 Context-Shift** (detail 63% left, context panel 37% right). Context panel (Zone 3) primitive is a `core-react-proposal`.
- Small, quick, non-destructive inline action → **Popover** via `IxQuickPopover` (never raw `Popover`).
- **Destructive or critical confirmation** → **Modal** via `@procore/core-react` `Modal` (Tier 2). Tier 3 (typed confirmation + cascade) is a `core-react-proposal`.

## Z-index canonical stack (enforced by `@procore/core-react`)

- `z-80` Unified Viewer — out of scope in this scaffold.
- `z-50` Modal — destructive confirmations; scrim `bg-black/50 fixed inset-0`.
- `z-30` Slide-Out (Tearsheet) — create / filter workflows; scrim `bg-white/30 absolute` inside workspace container only.
- `z-20` Popover — quick contextual interactions; NO scrim.
- `z-10` Tooltip — read-only hover info; NO scrim.
- `z-0` Shell — always present.

Do NOT set custom `zIndex` values. Use the primitives — they encode the stack.

## View-type to layout mapping

- **Home / Tool landing** → `toolLandingPage` Toolinator layout.
- **Detail** → `detailPage` Toolinator layout.
- **Settings** → `settingsPage` Toolinator layout.
- **Anchor view (list + detail)** → `SplitViewShell` template inside a `toolLandingPage` layout (Pattern 1 as a first-class `splitViewPage` layout is a `toolinator-proposal`).

